cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with object tracking and motion perception using 3D point clouds.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper focuses on automotive scenarios where accurate motion perception is critical.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the proposed approach is learning-based and uses a neural network for point cloud alignment.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes an AI-based approach for object-centric relative motion estimation.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with processing and aligning natural language data in the form of object labels.
